In article <1993Oct24.172852.22604@lokkur.dexter.mi.us> scs@lokkur.dexter.mi.us (Steve Simmons) writes:

}Agreed.  All we need is a standard header type for attaching signatures
}and modification to all existing news and mail software to create/honor
}it.  To do this properly, we need a new RFC at a minimum.

we already have it. it's called MIME (RFC 1341). most of the popular
internet mail and news readers have already been hacked to comply with
this standard.

all we need to do is incorporate the proper functionality into pgp.
some partial attempts at this have been made already (see the
directories contrib/{mh,mime} included with the pgp srcs.
